  "prompt": "Without any external help, how many pennies can you stack before the tower collapses?",
  "response": "The exact number of pennies you can stack before the tower collapses will vary depending on several factors such as the surface they are stacked on, the technique used to stack them, and external factors like wind or vibrations. \n\nGenerally, a well-stacked tower of pennies can reach around 30 to 50 pennies high before it becomes unstable and collapses. However, with careful stacking and optimizing the base, some individuals have been able to stack as many as 85 to 100 pennies in a stable formation on a flat, solid surface. \n\nIn summary, while there is no definitive answer and it can vary, with careful stacking, you may achieve around 30 to 100 pennies high.",
